  "text": "T HE USE OF mechanical resonators is widely extended in many applications, such as the measure of strain and mass change (gravimetric sensors) and as a part of inertial sensors, such as gyroscopes [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] or accelerometers [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] . Mechanical resonators may be excited by an external oscillator or may be a part of the oscillator itself (self-sustained oscillation).",
